When the termination reaction is not present in the polymerization of monomers, we call the polymerization is living polymerization. An important consequence of living polymerization is that the average degree of polymerization is simply equal to the ratio of the initial monomer concentration to the initiator concentration as shown in Eq. 7.73. There are different approaches to achieve living radical polymerizations which are discussed below.7.73\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
