Continuous solution polymerization is the most important method for the commercial production of polystyrene although suspension polymerization is also used. Emulsion polymerization is important for the synthesis of copolymer of acrylonitrile butadiene styrene(ABS). Commercial polystyrene (PS) has number-average molecular weights in the range of 50,000–150,000 with \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
